Matt,
speaking of relays, about a year ago I built your 9-pin signal replacement
and it worked great, (remember, I sent pics). During the winter I suffered
from what most do, leaky windshield seals, and collected water in the relays
and shut the system down. I pried apart the relay cans, drained the now
rusty rain water, cleaned the contacts and sprayed everything down with TV
contact silicone spray. Everything worked fine until my control broke. Now
that we are coming into another rainy season, what do you think about
applying silicone seal to the cans, will the seal siphon into the cans
during the dry period or do you think it will be OK ?

Need another 67 switch assembly too ! The last thing that operated was the
hi/lo beam relay before that went also. That was what jogged my memory when
I saw your e-mail.

